obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (21329)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21329&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi Development`
  line `Act, 1957.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the ^1[National Capital Territory of Delhi].`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Union territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `2 30th December, 1957, vide notification No. S. R. O. 120, dated 30th December, 1957, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part. II, sec. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (21330)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 2, for clause (l) (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21330&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "amenity" includes road, water supply, street lighting, drainage, sewerage, public works and`
  line `such other convenience as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify to be an amenity for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "building" includes any structure or erection or part of a structure or erection which is`
  line `intended to be used for residential, industrial, commercial or other purposes, whether in actual use or`
  line not;
  line
  line `(c) "building operations" includes rebuilding operations, structural alterations of or additions to`
  line `buildings and other operations normally undertaken in connection with the construction of buildings;`
  line
  line `(d) "development" with its grammatical variations means the carrying out of building,`
  line `engineering, mining or other operations in, on, over or under land or the making of any material`
  line `change in any building or land and includes redevelopment;`
  line
  line `(e) "development area" means any area declared to be a development area under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 12;`
  line
  line `(f) "engineering operations" includes the formation or laying out of means of access to a road or`
  line `the laying out of means of water supply;`
  line
  line `(g) "means of access" includes any means of access whether private or public, for vehicles or for`
  line `foot passengers, and includes a road;`
  line
  line `(h) "regulation" means a regulation made under this Act by the Delhi Development Authority`
  line `constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(i) "rule" means a rule made under this Act by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(j) "to erect" in relation to any building includes`
  line
  line `(i) any material alteration or enlargement of any building,`
  line
  line `(ii) the conversion by structural alteration into a place for human habitation of any building`
  line `not originally constructed for human habitation,`
  line
  line `(iii) the conversion into more than one place for human habitation of a building originally`
  line `constructed as one such place,`
  line
  line `(iv) the conversion of two or more places of human habitation into a greater number of such`
  line places,
  line
  line `(v) such alterations of a building as affect an alteration of its drainage or sanitary`
  line `arrangements, or materially affect its security,`
  line
  line `(vi) the addition of any rooms, buildings, houses or other structures to any building, and`
  line
  line `(vii) the construction in a wall adjoining any street or land not belonging to the owner of the`
  line `wall, of a door opening on to such street or land;`
  line
  line `(k) "zone" means any one of the divisions in which Delhi may be divided for the purposes of`
  line `development under this Act;`
  line
  line `^1[(l) the expression "land" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 3 of the Land`
  line `Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (21331)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `The Delhi Development Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21331&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the commencement of this Act,`
  line `the Central Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute for the purposes of this`
  line `Act an authority to be called the Delhi Development Authority (hereinafter referred to as the Authority).`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable and to`
  line `contract and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a chairman who shall be the ^1[Lieutenant Governor] of the ^2[National Capital Territory of`
  line `Delhi], ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) a vice-chairman to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) a finance and accounts member to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) an engineer member to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) as and when the Municipal Corporation of Delhi is established, two representatives of that`
  line `Corporation to be elected by the councillors and aldermen of the Corporation from among`
  line themselves;
  line
  line `^3[(f) three representatives of the Legislative Assembly of the National Capital Territory of Delhi`
  line `to be elected by means of a single transferable vote by the members of the Legislative Assembly from`
  line `among themselves of which two shall be from among the ruling party and one from the party in`
  line `opposition to the Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no member of the Council of Ministers for the Government of National Capital`
  line `Territory of Delhi shall be eligible to be elected to the Authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, "ruling party" and "party in opposition to`
  line `Government" shall mean the ruling party and the party in opposition to the Government recognised as`
  line `such by the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of the National Capital Territory of Delhi;]`
  line
  line `^4[(g) three other persons to be nominated by the Central Government, of whom one shall be a`
  line `person with experience of town planning or architecture; and]`
  line
  line `(h) the Commisioner of the Municipal Corporation of Delhi, ex officio.`
  line
  line `^5[(3A) The appointment of the vice-chairman may be either whole-time or part-time as the Central`
  line `Government may think fit but the appointment of the finance and accounts member and the engineer`
  line `member shall be whole-time.]`
  line
  line `^6[(4) The vice-chairman, if he is a whole-time member, the finance and accounts member and the`
  line `engineer member shall be entitled to receive from the funds of the Authority such salaries and such`
  line `allowances, if any, and governed by such conditions of service as may be determined by rules made in`
  line `this behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) The vice-chairman, if he is a part-time member, and other members specified in clause (e),`
  line `clause (f) and clause (g) of sub-section (3) may be paid from the funds of the Authority such allowances,`
  line `if any, as may be fixed by the Central Government in this behalf.]`
  line
  line `(6) The vice-chairman, the finance and accounts member, the engineer member and the ^7[three`
  line `members] referred to in clause (g) of sub-section (3) shall hold office during the pleasure of the Central`
  line `Government ^8***.`
  line
  line `^9[(7) An elected member shall hold office for a term of five years from the date of his election to the`
  line `Authority and shall be eligible for re-election:`
  line
  line `Provided that such term shall come to an end as soon as the member ceases to be a member of the`
  line `body from which he was elected.]`
  line
  line `(9) A member other than an ex officio member may resign his office by writing under his hand`
  line `addressed to the Central Government but shall continue in office until his resignation is accepted by that`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(10) No act or proceedings of the Authority shall be invalid by reason of the existence of any vacancy`
  line `in, or defect in the constitution of, the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Administrator" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Union territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (f) (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `4 Subs. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 3, for clause (g) (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `5 Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `6 Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for sub-sections (4) and (5) (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `7 Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "two members" (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `8. Certain words, brackets and letter omitted by Act 19 of 1966, s. 36 (w.e.f. 7-9-1966).`
  line
  line `9 Subs. by s. 36, ibid., for sub-sections (7) and (8) (w.e.f. 7-9-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (21332)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Staff of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21332&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may appoint two suitable persons`
  line `respectively as the secretary and the chief accounts officer of the Authority who shall exercise such`
  line `powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed by regulations or delegated to them by the`
  line `Authority or the chairman.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such control and restrictions as may be prescribed by rules, the Authority may appoint`
  line `such number of other officers and employees (including experts for technical work) as may be necessary`
  line `for the efficient performance of its functions and may determine their designations and grades.`
  line
  line `(3) The secretary, chief accounts officer and other officers and employees of the Authority shall be`
  line `entitled to receive from the funds of the Authority such salaries and such allowances, if any, and shall be`
  line `governed by such conditions of service as may be determined by regulations made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (21333)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21333&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall, as soon as may be, constitute an advisory council for`
  line `the purpose of advising the Authority on the preparation of the master plan and ^1[on such other matters`
  line `relating to the planning of development, or] arising out of, or in connection with, the administration of`
  line `this Act as may be referred to it by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The advisory council shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the chairman of the Authority, ex officio, who shall be the president;`
  line
  line `(b) two persons with knowledge of town planning or architecture to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(c) one representative of the Health Services of Delhi administration to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) four representatives of the Municipal Corporation of Delhi to be elected by the councillors`
  line `and aldermen from among themselves;`
  line
  line `^2[(e) two persons representing the Delhi Electric Supply Committee and the Delhi Water Supply`
  line `and Sewage Disposal Committee of the said Corporation, of whom--`
  line
  line `(i) one shall be elected by the members of the Delhi Electric Supply Committee from among`
  line `themselves; and`
  line
  line `(ii) one shall be elected by the members of the Delhi Water Supply and Sewage Disposal`
  line `Committee from among themselves;`
  line
  line `(ee) one representative of the Delhi Transport Corporation to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government;]
  line
  line `(f) three persons to be nominated by the Central Government of whom one shall represents the`
  line `interests of commerce and industry and one, the interests of labour, in Delhi;`
  line
  line `(g) four persons from the technical departments of the Central Government to be nominated by`
  line `that Government; and`
  line
  line `(h) three members of Parliament of whom two shall be members of the House of the People and`
  line `one shall be a member of the Council of States to be elected respectively by the members of the`
  line `House of the People and the members of the Council of States.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall meet as and when necessary and shall have the power to regulate its own`
  line procedure.
  line
  line `(4) An elected member shall hold office for a term of four years from the date of his election to the`
  line `council and shall be eligible for re-election:`
  line
  line `Provided that such term shall come to an end as soon as the member ceases to be a member of the`
  line `body from which he was elected.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 4, for certain words (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1984, s. 2, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 12-53-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (21334)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Constitution of committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 5 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21334&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Constitution of committees.--(1) The Authority may constitute as many committees`
  line `consisting wholly of members or wholly of other persons or partly of members and partly of other persons`
  line `and for such purpose or purposes as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) A committee constituted under this section shall meet at such time and place and shall observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be determined by`
  line `regulations made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The members of a committee (other than the members of the Authority) shall be paid such fees`
  line `and allowances for attending its meetings and for attending to any other work of the Authority, as may be`
  line `determined by regulations made in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (21335)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Objects of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21335&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The objects of the Authority shall be to promote and secure the`
  line `development of Delhi according to plan and for that purpose the Authority shall have the power to`
  line `acquire, hold, manage and dispose of land and other property, to carry out building, engineering, mining`
  line `and other operations, to execute works in connection with supply of water and electricity, disposal of`
  line `sewage and other services and amenities and generally to do anything necessary or expedient for purposes`
  line `of such development and for purposes incidental thereto:`
  line
  line `Provided that save as provided in this Act, nothing contained in this Act shall be construed as`
  line `authorising the disregard by the Authority of any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (21336)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Civic survey of, and master plan for, Delhi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 6 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21336&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall, as soon as may be, carry`
  line `out a civic survey of, and prepare a master plan for, Delhi.`
  line
  line `(2) The master plan shall--`
  line
  line `(a) define the various zones into which Delhi may be divided for the purposes of development`
  line `and indicate the manner in which the land in each zone is proposed to be used (whether by the`
  line `carrying out thereon of development or otherwise) and the stages by which any such development`
  line `shall be carried out; and`
  line
  line `(b) serve as a basic pattern of frame-work within which the zonal development plans of the`
  line `various zones may be prepared.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The master plan may provide for any other matter which is necessary for the proper`
  line `development of Delhi.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (21337)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Zonal development plans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21337&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Simultaneously with the preparation of the master plan or as soon`
  line `as may be thereafter, the Authority shall proceed with the preparation of a zonal development plan for`
  line `each of the zones into which Delhi may be divided.`
  line
  line `(2) A zonal development plan may--`
  line
  line `(a) contain a site-plan and use-plan for the development of the zone and show the approximate`
  line `locations and extents of land-uses proposed in the zone for such things as public buildings and other`
  line `public works and utilities, roads, housing, recreation, industry, business, markets, schools, hospitals`
  line `and public and private open spaces and other categories of public and private uses;`
  line
  line `(b) specify the standards of population density and building density;`
  line
  line `(c) show every area in the zone which may, in the opinion of the Authority, be required or`
  line `declared for development or redevelopment; and`
  line
  line `(d) in particular, contain provisions regarding all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the division of any site into plots for the erection of buildings;`
  line
  line `(ii) the allotment or reservation of land for roads, open spaces, gardens, recreation grounds,`
  line `schools, markets and other public purposes;`
  line
  line `(iii) the development of any area into a township or colony and the restrictions and conditions`
  line `subject to which such development may be undertaken or carried out;`
  line
  line `(iv) the erection of buildings on any site and the restrictions and conditions in regard to the`
  line `open spaces to be maintained in or around buildings and height and character of buildings;`
  line
  line `(v) the alignment of buildings on any site;`
  line
  line `(vi) the architectural features of the elevation or front age of any building to be erected on`
  line `any site;`
  line
  line `(vii) the number of residential buildings which may be erected on any plot or site;`
  line
  line `(viii) the amenities to be provided in relation to any site or buildings on such site whether`
  line `before or after the erection of buildings and the person or authority by whom or at whose expense`
  line `such amenities are to be provided;`
  line
  line `(ix) the prohibitions or restrictions regarding erection of shops, workshops, warehouses or`
  line `factories or buildings of a specified architectural feature or buildings designed for particular`
  line `purposes in the locality;`
  line
  line `(x) the maintenance of walls, fences, hedges or any other structural or architectural`
  line `construction and the height at which they shall be maintained;`
  line
  line `(xi) the restrictions regarding the use of any site for purposes other than erection of`
  line `buildings; and`
  line
  line `(xii) any other matter which is necessary for the proper development of the zone or any area`
  line `thereof according to plan and for preventing buildings being erected haphazardly in such zone or`
  line area.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (21338)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Submission of plans to the Central Government for approval.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21338&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this section and in`
  line `sections 10, 11, 12 and 14 the word "plan" means the master plan as well as the zonal development plan`
  line `for a zone.`
  line
  line `(2) Every plan shall, as soon as may be after its preparation, be submitted by the Authority to the`
  line `Central Government for approval and that Government may either approve the plan without modifications`
  line `or with such modifications as it may consider necessary or reject the plan with directions to the Authority`
  line `to prepare a fresh plan according to such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (21339)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Procedure to be followed in the preparation and approval of plans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21339&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before preparing any`
  line `plan finally and submitting it to the Central Government for approval, the Authority shall prepare a plan`
  line `in draft and publish it by making a copy thereof available for inspection and publishing a notice in such`
  line `form and manner as may be prescribed by rules made in this behalf inviting objections and suggestions`
  line `from any person with respect to the draft plan before such date as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall also give reasonable opportunities to every local authority within whose local`
  line `limits any land touched by the plan is situated, to make any representation with respect to the plan.`
  line
  line `(3) After considering all objections, suggestions and representations that may have been received by`
  line `the Authority, the Authority shall finally prepare the plan and submit it to the Central Government for its`
  line approval.
  line
  line `(4) Provisions may be made by rules made in this behalf with respect to the form and content of a`
  line `plan and with respect to the procedure to be followed and any other matter, in connection with the`
  line `preparation, submission and approval of such plan.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the foregoing provisions of this section the Central Government may direct the`
  line `Authority to furnish such information as that Government may require for the purpose of approving any`
  line `plan submitted to it under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (21340)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Date of operation of plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21340&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Immediately after a plan has been approved by the Central`
  line `Government, the Authority shall publish in such manner as may be prescribed by regulations a notice`
  line `stating that a plan has been approved and naming a place where a copy of the plan may be inspected at all`
  line `reasonable hours and upon the date of the first publication of the aforesaid notice the plan shall come into`
  line operation.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (21341)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 13
  title `Modifications to plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 7 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21341&sectionno=11A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Modifications to plan.--(1) The Authority may make any modifications to the master plan or`
  line `the zonal development plan as it thinks fit, being modifications which, in its opinion, do not effect`
  line `important alterations in the character of the plan and which do not relate to the extent of land-uses or the`
  line `standards of population density.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may make any modifications to the master plan or the zonal`
  line `development plan whether such modifications are of the nature specified in sub-section (1) or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(3) Before making any modifications to the plan, the Authority or, as the case may be, the Central`
  line `Government shall publish a notice in such form and manner as may be prescribed by rules made in this`
  line `behalf inviting objections and suggestions from any person with respect to the proposed modifications`
  line `before such date as may be specified in the notice and shall consider all objections and suggestions that`
  line `may be received by the Authority or the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Every modification made under the provisions of this section shall be published in such manner as`
  line `the Authority or the Central Government, as the case may be, may specify and the modifications shall`
  line `come into operation either on the date of the publication or on such other date as the Authority or the`
  line `Central Government may fix.`
  line
  line `(5) When the Authority makes any modifications to the plan under sub-section (1), it shall report to`
  line `the Central Government the full particulars of such modifications within thirty days of the date on which`
  line `such modifications come into operation.`
  line
  line `(6) If any question arises whether the modifications proposed to be made by the Authority are`
  line `modifications which effect important alterations in the character of the plan or whether they relate to the`
  line `extent of land-uses or the standards of population density, it shall be referred to the Central Government`
  line `whose decision thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(7) Any reference in any other Chapter, except Chapter III, to the master plan or the zonal`
  line `development plan shall be construed as a reference to the master plan or the zonal development plan as`
  line `modified under the provisions of this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (21342)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Declaration of development areas and development of land in those and other areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21342&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) As soon as may be after the commencement of this Act, the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, declare any area in Delhi to be a development area for the purposes of`
  line `this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such declaration shall be made unless a proposal for such declaration has been`
  line `referred by the Central Government to the Authority and the Municipal Corporation of Delhi for`
  line `expressing their views thereon within thirty days from the date of the receipt of the reference or within`
  line `such further period as the Central Government may allow and the period so specified or allowed has`
  line expired.]
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the Authority shall not undertake or carry out any`
  line `development of land in any area which is not a development area.`
  line
  line `(3) After the commencement of this Act no development of land shall be undertaken or carried out in`
  line `any area by any person or body (including a department of Government) unless,--`
  line
  line `(i) where that area is a development area, permission for such development has been obtained in`
  line `writing from the Authority in accordance with the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) where that area is an area other than a development area, approval of, or sanction for, such`
  line `development has been obtained in writing from the local authority concerned or any officer or`
  line `authority thereof empowered or authorised in this behalf, in accordance with the provisions made by`
  line `or under the law governing such authority or until such provisions have been made, in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of the regulations relating to the grant of permission for development made under`
  line `the Delhi (Control of Building Operations) Act, 1955 (53 of 1955), and in force immediately before`
  line `the commencement of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the local authority concerned may ^2[subject to the provisions of section 53A] amend`
  line `those regulations in their application to such area.`
  line
  line `(4) After the coming into operation of any of the plans in any area no development shall be`
  line `undertaken or carried out in that area unless such development is also in accordance with such plans.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (3) and (4) development of any land begun by`
  line `any department of Government or any local authority before the commencement of this Act may be`
  line `completed by that department or local authority without compliance with the requirements of those`
  line sub-sections.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 8, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (21343)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Application for permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21343&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person or body (including a department of Government)`
  line `desiring to obtain the permission referred to in section 12 shall make an application in writing to the`
  line `Authority in such form and containing such particulars in respect of the development to which the`
  line `application relates as may be prescribed by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed by`
  line `rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such fee shall be necessary in the case of an application made by a department of the`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) On the receipt of an application for permission under sub-section (1), the Authority after making`
  line `such inquiry as it considers necessary in relation to any matter specified in clause (d) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 8 or in relation to any other matter, shall, by order in writing, either grant the permission, subject`
  line `to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order or refuse to grant such permission:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making an order refusing such permission, the applicant shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to show cause why the permission should not be refused.`
  line
  line `(4) Where permission is refused, the grounds of such refusal shall be recorded in writing and`
  line `communicated to the applicant in the manner prescribed by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) The Authority shall keep in such form as may be prescribed by regulations a register of`
  line `applications for permission under this section.`
  line
  line `(6) The said register shall contain such particulars including information as to the manner in which`
  line `applications for permission have been dealt with as may be prescribed by regulations and shall be`
  line `available for inspection by any member of the public at all reasonable hours on payment of such fee not`
  line `exceeding rupees five as may be prescribed by regulations.`
  line
  line `(7) Where permission is refused under this section, the applicant or any person claiming through him`
  line `shall not be entitled to get refund of the fee paid on the application for permission but the Authority may,`
  line `on an application for refund being made within three months of the communication of the grounds of the`
  line `refusal under sub-section (4) direct refund of such portion of the fee as to it may seem proper in the`
  line `circumstances of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (21344)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `User of land and buildings in contravention of plans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21344&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `After the coming into operation of any`
  line `of the plans in a zone no person shall use or permit to be used any land or building in that zone otherwise`
  line `than in conformity with such plan:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be lawful to continue to use upon such terms and conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed by regulations made in this behalf any land or building for the purpose and to the extent for`
  line `and to which it is being used upon the date on which such plan comes into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (21345)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Compulsory acquisition of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 9, for section 15 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21345&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Compulsory acquisition of land.--(1) If in the opinion of the Central Government, any land is`
  line `required for the purpose of development, or for any other purpose, under this Act, the Central`
  line `Government may acquire such land under the provisions of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).`
  line `(2) Where any land has been acquired by the Central Government, that Government may, after it has`
  line `taken possession of the land, transfer the land to the Authority or any local authority for the purpose for`
  line `which the land has been acquired on payment by the Authority or the local authority of the compensation`
  line `awarded under that Act and of the charges incurred by the Government in connection with the`
  line acquisition.]
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (21346)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21346&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `[Compensation for compulsory acquisition of land.] Omitted by the Delhi Development`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1960 (56 of 1963), s. 10 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
