  sectionId (21351)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Disposal of land by the Authority or the local authority concerned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21351&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any`
  line `directions given by the Central Government under this Act, the Authority or, as the case may be, the local`
  line `authority concerned may dispose of--`
  line
  line `(a) any land acquired by the Central Government and transferred to it, without undertaking or`
  line `carrying out any development thereon; or`
  line
  line `(b) any such land after undertaking or carrying out such development as it thinks fit,`
  line
  line `to such persons, in such manner and subject to such terms and conditions as it considers expedient for`
  line `securing the development of Delhi according to plan.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers of the Authority or, as the case may be, the local authority concerned with respect to`
  line `the disposal of land under sub-section (1) shall be so exercised as to secure, so far as practicable, that`
  line `persons who are living or carrying on business or other activities on the land shall, if they desire to obtain`
  line `accommodation on land belonging to the Authority or the local authority concerned and are willing to`
  line `comply with any requirements of the Authority or the local authority concerned as to its development and`
  line `use, have an opportunity to obtain thereon accommodation suitable to their reasonable requirements on`
  line `terms settled with due regard to the price at which any such land has been acquired from them:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Authority or the local authority concerned proposes to dispose of by sale any`
  line `land without any development having been undertaken or carried out thereon, it shall offer the land in the`
  line `first instance to the persons from whom it was acquired, if they desire to purchase it subject to such`
  line `requirements as to its development and use as the Authority or the local authority concerned may think fit`
  line `to impose.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this Act shall be construed as enabling the Authority or the local authority concerned`
  line `to dispose of land by way of gift, mortgage or charge, but subject as aforesaid reference in this Act to the`
  line `disposal of land shall be construed as reference to the disposal thereof in any manner, whether by way of`
  line `sale, exchange or lease or by the creation of any easement right or privilege or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (21352)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Nazul lands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21352&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette and upon`
  line `such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon between that Government and the Authority, place at`
  line `the disposal of the Authority all or any developed and undeveloped lands in Delhi vested in the Union`
  line `(known and hereinafter referred to as nazul lands) for the purpose of development in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No development of any nazul land shall be undertaken or carried out except by, or under the`
  line `control and supervision of, the Authority after such land has been placed at the disposal of the Authority`
  line `under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) After any such nazul land has been developed by, or under the control and supervision of, the`
  line `Authority, it shall be dealt with by the Authority in accordance with rules made and directions given by`
  line `the Central Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) If any nazul land placed at the disposal of the Authority under sub-section (1) is required at any`
  line `time thereafter by the Central Government, the Authority shall, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `replace it at the disposal of that Government upon such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon`
  line `between that Government and the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (21353)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 25
  title `Power of Authority to develop land in non-development area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 11 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21353&sectionno=22A&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[22A. Power of Authority to develop land in non-development area.-- Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sub-section (2) of section 12, the Authority may, if it is of opinion that it is expedient to do`
  line `so, undertake or carry out any development of any land which has been transferred to it or placed at its`
  line `disposal under section 15 or section 22 even if such land is situate in any area which is not a development`
  line area.]
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (21354)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 26
  title `Fund of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21354&sectionno=23&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall have and maintain its own fund to which shall`
  line `be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys received by the Authority from the Central Government by way of grants, loans,`
  line `advances or otherwise;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) all moneys borrowed by the Authority from sources other than the Central Government by`
  line `way of loans or debentures;]`
  line
  line `(b) all fees and charges received by the Authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) all moneys received by the Authority from the disposal of lands, buildings and other`
  line `properties, movable and immovable; and`
  line
  line `(d) all moneys received by the Authority by way of rents and profits or in any other manner or`
  line `from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) The fund shall be applied towards meeting the expenses incurred by the Authority in the`
  line `administration of this Act and for no other purposes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority may keep in current account of the State Bank of India or any other bank approved`
  line `by the Central Government in this behalf such sum of money out of its fund as may be prescribed by rules`
  line `and any money in excess of the said sum shall be invested in such manner as may be approved by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, after due appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf,`
  line `make such grants, advances and loans to the Authority as that Government may deem necessary for the`
  line `performance of the functions of the Authority under this Act; and all grants, loans and advances made`
  line `shall be on such terms and conditions as the Central Government may determine.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) The Authority may borrow money by way of loans or debentures from such sources (other than`
  line `the Central Government) and on such terms and conditions as may be approved by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(6) The Authority shall maintain a sinking fund for the repayment of moneys borrowed under`
  line `sub-section (5), and shall pay every year into the sinking fund such sum as may be sufficient for`
  line `repayment within the period fixed of all moneys so borrowed.`
  line
  line `(7) The sinking fund or any part thereof shall be applied in, or towards, the discharge of the loan for`
  line `which such fund was created, and until such loan is wholly discharged it shall not be applied for any other`
  line purpose.]
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (21355)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 27
  title `Budget of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21355&sectionno=24&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Authority shall prepare in such form and at such time every year`
  line `as may be prescribed by rules a budget in respect of the financial year next ensuing showing the estimated`
  line `receipts and expenditure of the Authority and shall forward to the Central Government such number of`
  line `copies thereof as may be prescribed by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (21356)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 28
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21356&sectionno=25&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the balance-sheet in such form as the`
  line `Central Government may by rules prescribed in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line India.
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Authority shall be subject to audit annually by the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be`
  line `payable by the Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of accounts of the Authority shall have the same right, privilege and authority in connection`
  line `with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the audit of the`
  line `Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books, accounts,`
  line `connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the office of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Authority as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause a copy of the same to be laid before`
  line `both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (21357)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 29
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21357&sectionno=26&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Authority shall prepare for every year a report of its activities during that`
  line `year and submit the report to the Central Government in such form and on or before such date as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules, and that Government shall cause a copy of the report to be laid before both Houses of`
  line Parliament.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (21358)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 30
  title `Pension and provident funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21358&sectionno=27&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall constitute for the benefit of its`
  line `whole-time paid members and of its officers and other employees in such manner and subject to such`
  line `conditions, as may be prescribed by rules, such pension and provident funds as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any such pension or provident fund has been constituted, the Central Government may`
  line `declare that the provisions of the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925), shall apply to such fund as if it`
  line `were a Government Provident Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (21359)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 31
  title `Powers of entry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21359&sectionno=28&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may authorise any person to enter into or upon any land or`
  line `building with or without assistants or workmen for the purpose of--`
  line
  line `(a) making any enquiry, inspection, measurement or survey or taking levels of such land or`
  line building;
  line
  line `(b) examining works under construction and ascertaining the course of sewers and drains;`
  line
  line `(c) digging or boring into the sub-soil;`
  line
  line `(d) setting out boundaries and intended lines of work;`
  line
  line `(e) making such levels, boundaries and lines by placing marks and cutting trenches;`
  line
  line `(f) ascertaining whether any land is being or has been developed in contravention of the master`
  line `plan or zonal development plan or without the permission referred to in section 12 or in contravention`
  line `of any condition subject to which such permission has been granted; or`
  line
  line `(g) doing any other thing necessary for the efficient administration of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) no such entry shall be made except between the hours of sunrise and sunset and without`
  line `giving reasonable notice to the occupier, or if there be no occupier, to the owner of the land or`
  line building;
  line
  line `(ii) sufficient opportunity shall in every instance be given to enable women (if any) to`
  line `withdraw from such land or building;`
  line
  line `(iii) due regard shall always be had, so far as may be compatible with the exigencies of the`
  line `purpose for which the entry is made, to the social and religious usages of the occupants of the`
  line `land or building entered.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (21360)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 32
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21360&sectionno=29&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who whether at his own instance or at the instance of any other`
  line `person or any body (including a department of Government) undertakes or carries out development of any`
  line `land in contravention of the master plan or zonal development plan or without the permission, approval or`
  line `sanction referred to in section 12 or in contravention of any condition subject to which such permission,`
  line `approval or sanction has been granted, ^1[shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(a) with rigorous imprisonment which may extend to three years, if such development relates to`
  line `utilising, selling or otherwise dealing with any land with a view to the setting up of a colony without a`
  line `lay out plan; and`
  line
  line `(b) with simple imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to`
  line `five thousand rupees, or with both, in any case, other than those referred to in clause (a).]`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who uses any land or building in contravention of the provisions of section 14 or in`
  line `contravention of any terms and conditions prescribed by regulations under the proviso to that section shall`
  line `be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees ^2`
  line `[and in the case of a continuing`
  line `offence, with further fine which may extend to two hundred and fifty rupees for every day during which`
  line `such offence continues after conviction for the first commission of the offence].`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who obstructs the entry of a person authorised under section 28 to enter into or upon`
  line `any land or building or molests such person after such entry shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1984, s. 3, for certain words (w.e.f. 12-3-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 13 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (21361)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 33
  title `Order of demolition of building.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21361&sectionno=30&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Where any development has been commenced or is`
  line `being carried on or has been completed in contravention of the master plan or zonal development plan or`
  line `without the permission, approval or sanction referred to in section 12 or in contravention of any`
  line `conditions subject to which such permission, approval or sanction has been granted,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a development area, any officer of the Authority empowered by it in this behalf,`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other area within the local limits of a local authority, the competent`
  line `authority thereof,`
  line
  line `may, in addition to any prosecution that may be instituted under this Act, make an order, directing that`
  line `such development shall be removed by demolition, filling or otherwise by the owner thereof or by the`
  line `person at whose instance the development has been commenced or is being carried out or has been`
  line `completed, within such period (not being less than five days and more than fifteen days from the date on`
  line `which a copy of the order of removal, with a brief statement of the reasons therefor, has been delivered to`
  line `the owner or that person) as may be specified in the order and on his failure to comply with the order, the`
  line `officer of the Authority or, as the case may be, the competent authority may remove or cause to be`
  line `removed the development and the expenses of such removal shall be recovered from the owner or the`
  line `person at whose instance the development was commenced or was being carried out or was completed as`
  line `arrears of land revenue:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made unless the owner or the person concerned has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to show cause why the order should not be made.`
  line
  line `(1A) If any development in an area other than a development area has been commenced or is being`
  line `carried on or has been completed in contravention of the master plan or zonal development plan or`
  line `without the approval or sanction referred to in section 12 or in contravention of any conditions subject to`
  line `which such approval or sanction has been granted and the competent authority has failed to remove or`
  line `cause to be removed the development within the time that may be specified in this behalf by the`
  line `^2[Lieutenant Governor] of the ^3[National capital territory of Delhi], the ^2[Lieutenant Governor] may, after`
  line `observing such procedure as may be prescribed by rules made in this behalf, direct any officer to remove or cause to be removed such development and that officer shall be bound to carry out such direction and`
  line `any expenses of such removal may be recovered from the owner or the person at whose instance the`
  line `development was commenced or was being carried out or was completed as arrears of land revenue.]`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `^5[(2A) Any person aggrieved by the direction of the ^6[Lieutenant Governor] under sub-section (1A)`
  line `may appeal to the Central Government within thirty days from the date thereof, and the Central`
  line `Government may after giving an opportunity of hearing to the person aggrieved, either allow or dismiss`
  line `the appeal or may reverse or vary any part of the direction.]`
  line
  line `^7[(3) The decision of ^8[the Central Government on the appeal and subject only to such decision], the`
  line `direction under sub-section (1A), shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, any other provision`
  line `relating to demolition of buildings contained in any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Administrator" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Union territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by Act 38 of 1984, s. 4 (w.e.f. 12-5-1985).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 14 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Administrator" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 14, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 38 of 1984, s. 4, for certain words, brackets and figure (w.e.f. 12-5-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (21362)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to stop development.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21362&sectionno=31&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[31. Power to stop development.--(1) Where any development in any area has been commenced in`
  line `contravention of the master plan or zonal development plan or without the permission, approval or`
  line `sanction referred to in section 12 or in contravention of any conditions subject to which such permission,`
  line `approval or sanction has been granted,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a development area, the Authority or any officer of the Authority empowered by`
  line `it in this behalf,`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other area within the local limits of a local authority, the competent`
  line `authority thereof,`
  line
  line `may, in addition to any prosecution that may be instituted under this Act, make an order requiring the`
  line `development to be discontinued on and from the date of the service of the order, and such order shall be`
  line `complied with accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such development is not discontinued in pursuance of the order under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Authority or the officer of the Authority or the competent authority, as the case may be, may require any`
  line `police officer to remove the person by whom the development has been commenced and all his assistants`
  line `and workmen from the place of development ^2[or to seize any construction material, tool, machinery,`
  line `scaffolding or other things used in such development] within such time as may be specified in the`
  line `requisition and such police officer shall comply with the requisition accordingly.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) Any of the things caused to be seized by the Authority or the officer of the Authority or the`
  line `competent authority, as the case may be, under sub-section (2) shall, unless the owner thereof turns up to`
  line `take back such things and pays to the Authority, the officer of the Authority or the competent authority, as`
  line `the case may be, the charges for the removal or storage of such things, be disposed of by it or him by`
  line `public auction or in such other manner and within such time as the Authority, the officer of the Authority`
  line `or the competent authority thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2B) The charges for the removal and storage of the things sold under sub-section (2A) shall be paid`
  line `out of the proceeds of the sale thereof and the balance, if any, shall be paid to the owner of the things sold`
  line `on a claim being made therefor within a period of one year from the date of sale, and if no such claim is`
  line `made within the said period, shall be credited to the fund of the Authority or the competent authority, as`
  line `the case may be.]`
  line
  line `(3) If any development in an area other than a development area has been commenced in`
  line `contravention of the master plan or zonal development plan or without the approval or sanction referred to`
  line `in section 12 or in contravention of any conditions subject to which such approval or sanction has been`
  line `granted and the competent authority has failed to make an order under sub-section (1) or, as the case may`
  line `be, a requisition under sub-section (2), within the time that may be specified in this behalf by the`
  line `^3[Lieutenant Governor] of the ^4[National Capital Territory of Delhi], the ^3[Lieutenant Governor] may,`
  line `after observing such procedure as may be prescribed by rules made in this behalf, direct any officer to`
  line `make the order or requisition, as the case may be, and that officer shall be bound to carry out such`
  line `direction and the order or requisition made by him in pursuance of the direction shall be complied with`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(4) After the requisition under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) has been complied with,`
  line `the Authority or the competent authority or the officer to whom the direction was issued by the`
  line `^3[Lieutenant Governor] under sub-section (3), as the case may be, may depute by a written order a police`
  line `officer or an officer or employee of the Authority or local authority concerned to watch the place in order`
  line `to ensure that the development is not continued.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person failing to comply with an order under sub-section (1) or, as the case may be, under`
  line `sub-section (3), shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees for every day`
  line `during which the non-compliance continues after the service of the order.`
  line
  line `(6) No compensation shall be claimable by any person for any damage which he may sustain in`
  line `consequence of the removal of any development under section 30 or the discontinuance of the`
  line `development under this section.`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(8) The provisions of this section shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, any other provision`
  line `relating to stoppage of building operations contained in any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 15, for section 31 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 38 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 24-2-1986).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Administrator" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Union territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by Act 38 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 24-2-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (21363)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to seal unauthorised development.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21363&sectionno=31A&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^3[31A. Power to seal unauthorised development.--(1) It shall be lawful for the Authority or the`
  line `competent authority, as the case may be, at any time, before or after making an order for the removal or`
  line `discontinuance of any development under section 30 or section 31, to make an order directing the sealing`
  line `of such development in the manner prescribed by rules, for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of`
  line `this Act, or for preventing any dispute as to the nature and extent of such development.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any development has been sealed, the Authority or the competent authority, as the case`
  line `may be, may, for the purpose of removing or discontinuing such development order the seal to be`
  line removed.
  line
  line `(3) No person shall remove such seal except--`
  line
  line `(a) under an order made by the Authority or the competent authority under sub-section (2); or`
  line
  line `(b) under an order of the Appellate Tribunal or the ^1[Lieutenant Governor] of the ^2[National`
  line `Capital Territory of Delhi], made in an appeal under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Administrator" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Union territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-2-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_b:
  sectionId (21364)
  sectionNo 31B
  orderNo 36
  title `Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-2-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21364&sectionno=31B&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_31_b_content:
  string
  line `^131B. Appellate Tribunal.--The Appellate Tribunal or Appellate Tribunals constituted under`
  line `section 347A of the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957, (66 of 1957) shall be deemed to be the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal or Appellate Tribunals for deciding appeals under section 31C, and the provisions of`
  line `section 347A and section 347C of the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957, and the rules made`
  line `thereunder, shall, so far as may be, apply for the purposes of this Act as they apply for the purposes of`
  line `that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_c:
  sectionId (21365)
  sectionNo 31C
  orderNo 37
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-2-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21365&sectionno=31C&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_31_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[31C. Appeals.--(1) Any person aggrieved by any of the following orders made under this Act, may`
  line `prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) an order of the Authority granting or refusing to grant permission for development under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(b) an order of the Authority or the local authority disposing of any land under section 21;`
  line
  line `(c) an order of the Authority in the course of dealing with any nazul land developed by it under`
  line `section 22;`
  line
  line `(d) an order of an officer of the Authority or the competent authority made under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 30, for the removal of any development;`
  line
  line `(e) an order of the Authority or an officer of the Authority, or the competent authority made under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 31, for discontinuing any development;`
  line
  line `(f) an order of the Authority or the competent authority made under section 31A, directing the`
  line `sealing of any development.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal under this section shall be filed within thirty days from the date of the order appealed`
  line `against:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be made in such form and shall be accompanied by a`
  line `copy of the order appealed against and by such fees as may be prescribed by rules.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_d:
  sectionId (21366)
  sectionNo 31D
  orderNo 38
  title `Appeals against orders of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21366&sectionno=31D&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_31_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[31D. Appeals against orders of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) An appeal shall lie to the ^2[Lieutenant`
  line `Governor] of the ^3[National Capital Territory of Delhi] against an order of the Appellate Tribunal,`
  line `confirming, modifying or annulling an order of the Authority, officer of the Authority, local authority or`
  line `competent authority, as the case may be, under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 31C and the provisions of section 347C of`
  line `the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957 (66 of 1957), and the rules made thereunder, shall, so far as`
  line `may be, apply to the filing and disposal of an appeal under this section as they apply to the filing and`
  line `disposal of an appeal under the said section 31C.`
  line
  line `(3) An order of the ^2[Lieutenant Governor] on an appeal under this section, and subject only to such`
  line `order, an order of the Appellate Tribunal under section 31C and subject to such orders of the ^2[Lieutenant`
  line `Governor] or an Appellate Tribunal, an order of the Authority, officer of the Authority, local authority or`
  line `competent authority referred to in sub-section (1) of that section shall be final.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In sections 30, 31, 31A and 31D, "competent authority" in relation to a local authority`
  line `means any authority or officer of that local authority empowered or authorised to order demolition or`
  line `stoppage of buildings or works, in accordance with the provisions made by or under the law governing`
  line `such local authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-2-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Administrator" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Union territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_e:
  sectionId (21367)
  sectionNo 31E
  orderNo 39
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-2-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21367&sectionno=31E&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_31_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[31E. Bar of jurisdiction of courts.--(1) After the commencement of section 6 of the Delhi`
  line `Development (Amendment) Act, 1984 (38 of 1984), no court shall entertain any suit, application or other`
  line `proceedings in respect of any order appealable under section 31C, and no such order shall be called in`
  line `question otherwise than by preferring an appeal under that section.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), every suit, application or other proceeding`
  line `pending in any court immediately before the commencement of section 6 of the Delhi Development`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1984 (38 of 1984), in respect of any order, appealable under section 31C shall`
  line `continue to be dealt with and disposed of by that court as if the said section had not been brought into`
  line force.]
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (21368)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 40
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21368&sectionno=32&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing an offence under this Act is a company,`
  line `every person, who, at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible to, the`
  line `company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (21369)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 41
  title `Fines when realised to be paid to Authority or local authority concerned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21369&sectionno=33&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `All fines realised`
  line `in connection with prosecutions under this Act shall be paid to the Authority or, as the case may be, the`
  line `local authority concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (21370)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 42
  title `Composition of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21370&sectionno=34&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Any offence made punishable by or under this Act may, either`
  line `before or after the institution of proceedings, be compounded--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of an offence referred to in sub-section (2) of section 49, by the ^2[Lieutenant`
  line `Governor] of the ^3[National Capital territory of Delhi] or any officer authorised by him in this behalf`
  line `by general or special order; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, by the Authority or, as the case may be, the local authority concerned or any`
  line `person authorised by the Authority or such local authority by general or special order in this behalf.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence has been compounded, the offender, if in custody shall be discharged and no`
  line `further proceedings shall be taken against him in respect of the offence compounded.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 16, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Administrator" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Union territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_34_a:
  sectionId (21371)
  sectionNo 34A
  orderNo 43
  title `Certain offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21371&sectionno=34A&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content:
  string
  line `^3[34A. Certain offences to be cognizable.-- The Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),`
  line `shall apply to an offence under sub-section (1) of section 29 as if it were a cognizable offence,--`
  line
  line `(i) for the purposes of investigation of such offence, and`
  line
  line `(ii) for the purposes of all matters other than--`
  line
  line `(1) matters referred to in section 42 of that Code, and`
  line
  line `(2) arrest of a person except on the complaint of, or upon information received from:--`
  line
  line `(a) such officer of the Authority not below the rank of a Director as may be appointed by`
  line `the ^1`
  line `[Lieutenant Governor] of the ^2`
  line `[National capital territory of Delhi], if the offence is`
  line `committed in relation to a development area;`
  line
  line `(b) such officer of the Municipal Corporation of Delhi not below the rank of a Deputy`
  line `Commissioner as may be appointed by the ^1`
  line `[Lieutenant Governor] of the ^2`
  line `[National capital`
  line `territory of Delhi], if the offence is committed in relation to any area within the local limits of`
  line `that Corporation; or`
  line
  line `(c) the Secretary, New Delhi Municipal Committee, if the offence is committed in`
  line `relation to any area within the local limits of that Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that no offence which relates to any deviation from the permission, approval or sanction`
  line `given under section 12 and which could be compounded under the provisions of this Act, shall be`
  line cognizable.]
obj_root_law_sections_34_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Administrator" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Union territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 38 of 1984, s. 7 (w.e.f. 24-2-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (21372)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 44
  title `Default powers of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 17, for section 35 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21372&sectionno=35&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `^1[35. Default powers of the Authority.--(1) If the Authority, after holding a local enquiry or upon`
  line `report from any of its officers or other information in its possession, is satisfied that any amenity in`
  line `relation to any land in a development area has not been provided in relation to that land which in the`
  line `opinion of the Authority is to be provided, or that any development of the land for which permission,`
  line `approval or sanction has been obtained under this Act has not been carried out, it may, after affording a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to show cause, serve upon the owner of the land or upon the person providing or`
  line `responsible for providing the amenity a notice requiring him to provide the amenity or carry out the`
  line `development within such time as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If any amenity is not provided or any such development is not carried out within the time`
  line `specified in the notice, then the Authority may itself provide the amenity or carry out the development or`
  line `have it provided or carried out through such agency as it deems fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that before taking any action under this sub-section, the Authority shall afford reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the owner of the land or to the person providing or responsible for providing the amenity to`
  line `show cause as to why such action should not be taken.`
  line
  line `(3) All expenses incurred by the Authority or the agency employed by it in providing the amenity or`
  line `carrying out the development together with interest at such rate as the Central Government may by order`
  line `fix from the date when a demand for the expenses is made until payment may be recovered by the`
  line `Authority from the owner or the person providing or responsible for providing the amenity as arrears of`
  line `land revenue.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (21373)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power of Authority to require local authority to assume responsibility for amenities in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21373&sectionno=36&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Where any area has been developed by the Authority, the Authority may require the local`
  line `authority within whose local limits the area so developed is situated, to assume responsibility for the`
  line `maintenance of the amenities which have been provided in the area by the Authority and for the provision`
  line `of the amenities which have not been provided by the Authority but which in its opinion should be`
  line `provided in the area, on terms and conditions agreed upon between the Authority and that local authority;`
  line `and where such terms and conditions cannot be agreed upon, on terms and conditions settled by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with the local authority on a reference of the matter to that`
  line `Government by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (21374)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power of Authority to levy betterment charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for section 37 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21374&sectionno=37&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1[37. Power of Authority to levy betterment charges.--(1) Where, in the opinion of the Authority,`
  line `as a consequence of any development having been executed by the Authority in any development area,`
  line `the value of any property in that area or in any area other than the development area, which has been`
  line `benefited by the development, has increased or will increase, the Authority shall be entitled to levy upon`
  line `the owner of the property or any person having an interest therein a betterment charge in respect of the`
  line `increase in value of the property resulting from the execution of the development:`
  line
  line `Provided that no betterment charge shall be levied in respect of lands owned by Government within`
  line `Delhi:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where any land belonging to Government has been let out by Government to`
  line `any person, then that land and any building situate thereon shall be subject to a betterment charge under`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Such betterment charge shall be an amount`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of any property situate in a development area, equal to one-third of the amount, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in respect of property situate in any other area, not exceeding one-third of the amount, by which the value of the property on the completion of the execution of the development scheme`
  line `estimated as if the property were clear of buildings exceeds the value of the property prior to such`
  line `execution estimated in like manner:`
  line
  line `Provided that in levying betterment charge on any property under clause (ii), the Authority shall have`
  line `regard to the extent and nature of benefit accruing to the property from the development and such other`
  line `factors as may be prescribed by rules made in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (21375)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 47
  title `Assessment of betterment charge by Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21375&sectionno=38&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) When it appears to the Authority that any`
  line `particular development scheme is sufficiently advanced to enable the amount of the betterment charge to`
  line `be determined, the Authority may, by an order made in this behalf, declare that for the purpose of`
  line `determining the betterment charge the execution of the scheme shall be deemed to have been completed`
  line `and shall thereupon give notice in writing to the owner of the property or any person having an interest`
  line `therein that the Authority proposes to assess the amount of the betterment charge in respect of the`
  line `property under section 37.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall then assess the amount of betterment charge payable by the person concerned`
  line `after giving such person an opportunity to be heard and such person shall, within three months from the`
  line `date of receipt of the notice in writing of such assessment from the Authority, inform the Authority by a`
  line `declaration in writing that he accepts the assessment or dissents from it.`
  line
  line `(3) When the assessment proposed by the Authority is accepted by the person concerned within the`
  line `period specified in sub-section (2) such assessment shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) If the person concerned dissents from the assessment or fails to give the Authority the information`
  line `required by sub-section (2) within the period specified therein the matter shall be determined by`
  line `arbitrators in the manner provided in section 39.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (21376)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 48
  title `Settlement of betterment charge by arbitrators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1.Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 19 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21376&sectionno=39&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the determination of the matter`
  line `referred to in sub-section (4) of section 38, the Central Government shall appoint three arbitrators of`
  line `whom one at least shall have special knowledge of the valuation of land.`
  line
  line `(2) The arbitrators shall follow such procedure as may be prescribed by rules made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `^1[(2A) The arbitrators shall, for the purpose of determining any matter referred to them, have the same`
  line `powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) when trying a`
  line `suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) administering to any party to the arbitration such interrogatories as may, in the opinion of the`
  line `arbitrators, be necessary.]`
  line
  line `(3) In the event of any difference of opinion among the arbitrators the decision of the majority shall`
  line `prevail and that decision shall be the award of the arbitrators.`
  line
  line `(4) If any arbitrator dies, resigns, or is removed under sub-section (5) or refuses, or neglects in the`
  line `opinion of the Central Government, to perform his duties or becomes incapable of performing the same,`
  line `then the Central Government shall forthwith appoint another fit person to take the place of such arbitrator.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Central Government is satisfied after such inquiry as it thinks fit--`
  line
  line `(a) that an arbitrator has misconducted himself, the Central Government may remove him from`
  line `his office;`
  line
  line `(b) that the award of the arbitrators has been improperly procured or that any arbitrator has`
  line `misconducted himself in connection with such award, the Central Government may set aside the`
  line award.
  line
  line `(6) An Award which has not been set aside by the Central Government under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (5) shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court.`
  line
  line `(7) The provisions of the Arbitration Act, 1940 (10 of 1940), shall not apply to arbitration under this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (21377)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 49
  title `Payment of betterment charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21377&sectionno=40&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The betterment charge levied under this Act shall be`
  line `payable in such number of instalments and each instalment shall be payable at such time and in such`
  line `manner as may be fixed by regulations made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Any arrear of betterment charge shall be recoverable as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40_a:
  sectionId (21378)
  sectionNo 40A
  orderNo 50
  title `Mode of recovery of moneys due to Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 20 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21378&sectionno=40A&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_40_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[40A. Mode of recovery of moneys due to Authority.--Any money due to the Authority on`
  line `account of fees or charges, or from the disposal of lands, buildings or other properties, movable or`
  line `immovable, or by way of rents and profits may, if the recovery thereof is not expressly provided for in`
  line `any other provision of this Act, be recovered by the Authority as arrears of land revenue.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (21379)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 51
  title `Control by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21379&sectionno=41&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall carry out such directions as may be`
  line `issued to it from time to time by the Central Government for the efficient administration of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If in, or in connection with, the exercise of its powers and discharge of its functions by the`
  line `Authority under this Act, any dispute arises between the Authority and the Central Government the`
  line `decision of the Central Government on such dispute shall be final.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The Central Government may, at any time, either on its own motion or on application made to it`
  line `in this behalf, call for the records of any case disposed of or order passed by the Authority for the purpose`
  line `of satisfying itself as to the legality or propriety of any order passed or direction issued and may pass such`
  line `order or issue such direction in relation thereto as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall not pass an order prejudicial to any person without`
  line `affording such person a reasonable opportunity of being heard.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (21380)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 52
  title `Returns and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for section 42 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21380&sectionno=42&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `^1[42. Returns and inspection.--(1) The Authority shall furnish to the Central Government such`
  line `reports, returns and other information as that Government may from time to time require.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Central Government or any officer`
  line `authorised by the Central Government in this behalf, may call for reports, returns and other information`
  line `from the Authority or local authority in regard to the implementation of the master plan.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person authorised by the Central Government or the officer referred to in sub-section (2) may`
  line `enter into or upon any land with or without assistants or workmen for ascertaining whether the provisions`
  line `of the master plan are being or have been implemented, or whether the development is being or has been`
  line `carried out in accordance with such plan.`
  line
  line `(4) No such entry shall be made except between the hours of sunrise and sunset and without giving`
  line `reasonable notice to the occupier, or if there be no occupier, to the owner of the land or building.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (21381)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 53
  title `Service of notices, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Union territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21381&sectionno=43&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) All notices, orders and other documents required by this Act or any`
  line `rule or regulation made thereunder to be served upon any person shall, save as otherwise provided in this`
  line `Act or such rule or regulation, be deemed to be duly served--`
  line
  line `(a) where the person to be served is a company if the document is addressed to the secretary of`
  line `the company at its registered office or at its principal office or place of business and is either--`
  line
  line `(i) sent by registered post, or`
  line
  line `(ii) delivered at the registered office or at the principal office or place of business of the`
  line company;
  line
  line `(b) where the person to be served is a partnership, if the document is addressed to the partnership`
  line `at its principal place of business, identifying it by the name or style under which its business is carried`
  line `on, and is either--`
  line
  line `(i) sent by registered post, or`
  line
  line `(ii) delivered at the said place of business;`
  line
  line `(c) where the person to be served is a public body or a corporation or society or other body, if the`
  line `document is addressed to the secretary, treasurer or other head officer of that body, corporation or`
  line `society at its principal office, and is either--`
  line
  line `(i) sent by registered post, or`
  line
  line `(ii) delivered at that office;`
  line
  line `(d) in any other case, if the document is addressed to the person to be served and--`
  line
  line `(i) is given or tendered to him, or`
  line
  line `(ii) if such person cannot be found, is affixed on some conspicuous part of his last known`
  line `place of residence or business, if within the ^1`
  line `[National captial territory of Delhi] or is given or`
  line `tendered to some adult member of his family or is affixed on some conspicuous part of the land or`
  line `building to which it relates, or`
  line
  line `(iii) is sent by registered post to that person.`
  line
  line `(2) Any document which is required or authorised to be served on the owner or occupier of any land`
  line `or building may be addressed the owner or the occupier, as the case may be, of that land or building`
  line `(naming that land or building) without further name or description, and shall be deemed to be duly`
  line served--
  line
  line `(a) if the document so addressed is sent or delivered in accordance with clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1); or`
  line
  line `(b) if the document so addressed or a copy thereof so addressed, is delivered to some person on`
  line `the land or building or, where there is no person on the land or building to whom it can be delivered,`
  line `is affixed to some conspicuous part of the land or building.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a document is served on a partnership in accordance with this section, the document shall`
  line `be deemed to be served on each partner.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of enabling any document to be served on the owner of any property the secretary`
  line `to the Authority may by notice in writing require the occupier (if any) of the property to state the name`
  line `and address of the owner thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the person on whom a document is to be served is a minor, the service upon his guardian or`
  line `any adult member of his family shall be deemed to be service upon the minor.`
  line
  line `(6) A servant is not a member of the family within the meaning of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (21382)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 54
  title `Public notice how to be made known.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21382&sectionno=44&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Every public notice given under this Act shall be in`
  line `writing over the signature of the secretary to the Authority and shall be widely made known in the locality`
  line `to be affected thereby by affixing copies thereof in conspicuous public places within the said locality, or`
  line `by publishing the same by beat of drum or by advertisement in local newspaper or by any two or more of`
  line `these means, and by any other means that the secretary may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (21383)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 55
  title `Notices, etc., to fix reasonable time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21383&sectionno=45&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Where any notice, order or other document issued or`
  line `made under this Act or any rule or regulation made thereunder requires anything to be done for the doing`
  line `of which no time is fixed in this Act or the rule or regulation, the notice, order or other document shall`
  line `specify a reasonable time for doing the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (21384)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 56
  title `Authentication of orders and documents of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21384&sectionno=46&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `All permissions, orders, decisions,`
  line `notices and other documents of the Authority shall be authenticated by the signature of the secretary to`
  line `the Authority or any other officer authorised by the Authority in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (21385)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 57
  title `Members and officers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21385&sectionno=47&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Every member and every officer and other`
  line `employee of the Authority shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (21386)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 58
  title `Jurisdiction of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1984, s. 8, for "magistrate of the first class" (w.e.f. 12-3-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21386&sectionno=48&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a ^1[Metropolitan Magistrate] shall try an`
  line `offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (21387)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 59
  title `Sanction of prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21387&sectionno=49&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] No prosecution for any offence punishable under this Act`
  line `^2[other than an offence referred to in sub-section (2)] shall be instituted except with the previous sanction`
  line `of the Authority or as the case may be, the local authority concerned or any officer authorised by the`
  line `Authority or such local authority in this behalf.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) No prosecution for any offence for failure to comply with the order of the officer referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 31 and punishable under sub-section (5) of that section shall be instituted except`
  line `with the previous sanction of the ^3[Lieutenant Governor] or any officer authorised by him in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 49 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by Act 56 of 1963, s. 23 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Administrator" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (21388)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 60
  title `Magistrate’s power to impose enhanced penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 38 of 1984, s. 9, for certain words and figures (w.e.f. 12-3-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21388&sectionno=50&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in ^1[section 29 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), it shall be lawful for any court of a`
  line `Metropolitan Magistrate] to pass any sentence authorised by this Act in excess of its powers under the`
  line `said section.`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (21389)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 61
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21389&sectionno=51&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or`
  line `any rule or regulation made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (21390)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21390&sectionno=52&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `^2[(1)] The Authority may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that`
  line `any power exercisable by it under this Act except the power to make regulations may also be exercised by`
  line `such officer or local authority ^[or committee constituted under section 5A] as may be mentioned therein,`
  line `in such cases and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified therein.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any power`
  line `exercisable by it under this Act, except the power to make rules, may also be exercised by such officer as`
  line `may be mentioned therein, in such cases and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(3) The ^1[Lieutenant Governor] of the ^4[National capital territory of Delhi] may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, direct that any power exercisable by him under this Act ^5[, except the power to hear`
  line `appeals,] may also be exercised by such officer as may be mentioned therein, in such cases and subject to`
  line `such conditions, if any, as may be specified therein.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Administrator" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `2. Section 52 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by Act 56 of 1963, s. 23 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Union territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 38 of 1984, s. 10 (w.e.f. 24-2-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (21391)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 63
  title `Effect of other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 25, for "Save as aforesaid" (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21391&sectionno=53&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this Act shall affect the operation of the Slum Areas`
  line `(Improvement and Clearance) Act, 1956 (6 of 1956).`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^1[Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (4) of section 30 or sub-section (8) of section 31 or`
  line `sub-section (1)' of this section, the provisions of this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder`
  line `shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any such other law--`
  line
  line `(a) when permission for development in respect of any land has been obtained under this Act`
  line `such development shall not be deemed to be unlawfully undertaken or carried out by reason only of`
  line `the fact that permission, approval or sanction required under such other law for such development has`
  line `not been obtained;`
  line
  line `(b) when permission for such development has not been obtained under this Act, such`
  line `development shall not be deemed to be lawfully undertaken or carried out by reason only of the fact`
  line `that permission, approval or sanction required under such other law for such development has been`
  line obtained.
obj_root_law_sections_53_a:
  sectionId (21392)
  sectionNo 53A
  orderNo 64
  title `Restriction on power of a local authority to make rules, regulations or bye-laws in respect of certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 26 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21392&sectionno=53A&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[53A. Restriction on power of a local authority to make rules, regulations or bye-laws in`
  line `respect of certain matters.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in`
  line `force, no rule, regulation or bye-law shall be made or amended by a local authority in respect of matters`
  line `specified in sub-section (2) unless the Authority, upon consideration of such rule, regulation or bye-law,`
  line `certifies that it does not contravene any of the provisions of the master plan or the zonal development`
  line plan.
  line
  line `(2) The matters referred to in sub-section (1) are the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) water supply, drainage and sewage disposal;`
  line
  line `(b) erection and re-erection of buildings, including grant of building permissions, licences and`
  line `imposition of restrictions on use and sub-division of buildings;`
  line
  line `(c) sub-division of land into building sites, roads and lanes, recreational sites and sites for`
  line `community facilities; and`
  line
  line `(d) development of land, improvement schemes, and housing and rehousing schemes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_b:
  sectionId (21393)
  sectionNo 53B
  orderNo 65
  title `Notice to be given of suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 26 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21393&sectionno=53B&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_53_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[53B. Notice to be given of suits.--(1) No suit shall be instituted against the Authority, or any`
  line `member thereof, or any of its officers or other employees, or any person acting under the directions of the`
  line `Authority or any member or any officer or other employee of the Authority in respect of any act done or`
  line `purporting to have been done in pursuance of this Act or any rule or regulation made thereunder until the`
  line `expiration of two months after notice in writing has been, in the case of the Authority, left at its office,`
  line `and in any other case, delivered to, or left at the office or place of abode of, the person to be sued and`
  line `unless such notice states explicitly the cause of action, the nature of relief sought, the amount of`
  line `compensation claimed and the name and place of residence of the intending plaintiff and unless the plaint`
  line `contains a statement that such notice has been so left or delivered.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit such as is described in sub-section (1) shall, unless it is a suit for recovery of immovable`
  line `property or for a declaration of title thereto, be instituted after the expiry of six months from the date on`
  line `which the cause of action arises.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to apply to a suit in which the only relief`
  line `claimed is an injunction of which the object would be defeated by the giving of the notice or the`
  line `postponement of the institution of the suit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (21394)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 66
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21394&sectionno=54&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) the carrying out of works for the maintenance, improvement or other alteration of any`
  line `building, being works which affect only the interior of the building or which do not materially affect`
  line `the external appearance of the building;`
  line
  line `(b) the carrying out by any local authority or by any department of Government of any works for`
  line `the purpose of inspecting, repairing or renewing any drains, sewers, mains, pipes, cables or other`
  line `apparatus including the breaking open of any street or other land for that purpose;`
  line
  line `(c) the erection of a building, not being a dwelling house if such building is required for the`
  line `purposes subservient to agriculture;`
  line
  line `(d) the erection of a place of worship or a tomb or cenotaph or of a wall enclosing a graveyard,`
  line `place of worship, cenotaph or samadhi on land which at the commencement of this Act is occupied`
  line `by or for the purpose of such worship, tomb, cenotaph, graveyard or samadhi;`
  line
  line `(e) the excavations (including wells) made in the ordinary course of agricultural operations; and`
  line
  line `(f) the construction of unmetalled road intended to give access to land solely for agricultural`
  line purposes.
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (21395)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 67
  title `Plans to stand modified in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21395&sectionno=55&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any land situated in any area in Delhi is`
  line `required by the master plan or a zonal development plan to be kept as an open space or unbuilt upon or is`
  line `designated in any such plan as subject to compulsory acquisition, then, if at the expiration of ten years`
  line `from the date of operation of the plan under section 11 or where such land has been so required or`
  line `designated by any amendment of such plan, from the date of operation of such amendment, the land is not`
  line `compulsorily acquired ^1***, the owner of the land may ^2[serve on the Central Government a notice]`
  line `requiring his interest in the land to be so acquired.`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^3[If the Central Government] fails to acquire the land within a period of six months from the date`
  line `of receipt of the notice, the master plan or, as the case may be, the zonal development plan shall have`
  line `effect, after the expiration of the said six months as if the land were not required to be kept as an open`
  line `space or unbuilt upon or were not designated as subject to compulsory acquisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Certain words omitted by Act 56 of 1963, s. 27 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for "serve on the authority a notice" (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for "If the authority for the time being charged with the development of the area" (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (21396)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 68
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21396&sectionno=56&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government, after consultation with the Authority, may`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that consultation with the Authority shall not be necessary on the first occasion of the`
  line `making of rules under this section, but the Central Government shall take into consideration any`
  line `suggestions which the Authority may make in relation to the amendment of such rules after they are`
  line made.
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of election of representatives of the Municipal Corporation of Delhi under`
  line `clause (e) of sub-section (3) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the qualifications and disqualifications for being chosen as, and for being, members of the`
  line `Authority or the Advisory Council;`
  line
  line `(c) the salaries, allowances and conditions of service of the whole-time paid members of the`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `^1[(cc) travelling and other allowances of the members of the Advisory Council except those of the`
  line `ex officio member and such other members as are Government servants;]`
  line
  line `(d) the control and restrictions in relation to appointment of officers and other employees;`
  line
  line `^2[(dd) the stages by which the development of any particular features of a zone may be carried`
  line out;]
  line
  line `(e) the form and content of the master plan and a zonal development plan and the procedure to be`
  line `followed in connection with the preparation, submission and approval of such plans and the form, and`
  line `the manner of publication, of the notice relating to any such plan in draft;`
  line
  line `(f) the local inquiries and other hearings that may be held before a plan is approved;`
  line
  line `^3[(g) the form and manner in which notice under sub-section (3) of section 11A shall be`
  line published;]
  line
  line `(h) the fee to be paid on an application for permission under sub-section (1) of section 13 and the`
  line `factors and circumstances to be taken into consideration in determining such fee;`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(j) the manner in which nazul lands shall be dealt with after development;`
  line
  line `^5[(jj) the procedure to be observed by the ^6[ Lieutenant Governor] under section 30 or section 31;`
  line
  line `(jjj) the factors to be taken into consideration in determining the rate of betterment charge in`
  line `respect of property situate in any area outside the development area;]`
  line
  line `^7[(ja) the manner in which the sealing of any development under sub-section (1) of section 31A`
  line `shall be made;`
  line
  line `(jb) the form in which an appeal shall be made to the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 31C and the fees that shall accompany such appeal;]`
  line
  line `(k) the procedure for referring any matter to the Central Government under section 36 for`
  line `settlement of terms and conditions subject to which a local authority may be required to assume`
  line `responsibility for amenities in any area;`
  line
  line `(l) the procedure to be followed by arbitrators in the determination of betterment charge;`
  line
  line `(m) the sum of money that may be kept in current account;`
  line
  line `^5[(mm) the procedure to be followed for borrowing moneys by way of loans or debentures and`
  line `their repayment;]`
  line
  line `(n) the form of the budget of the Authority and the manner of preparing the same;`
  line
  line `(o) the form of the balance-sheet and statement of accounts;`
  line
  line `(p) the form of the annual report and the date on or before which it shall be submitted to the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(q) the manner of constitution of the pension and provident funds for whole-time paid members`
  line `and officers and other employees of the Authority and the conditions subject to which such funds may`
  line `be constituted;`
  line
  line `(r) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1976, s. 2 (w.e.f. 24-1-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 28 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 28, for clause (g) (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Administrator" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 38 of 1984, s. 11 (w.e.f. 24-2-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (21397)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 69
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21397&sectionno=57&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^1[The Authority, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations] consistent with this Act and`
  line `the rules made thereunder, to carry out the purposes of this Act, and without prejudice to the generality of`
  line `this power, such regulations may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the summoning and holding of meetings of the Authority, the time and place where such`
  line `meetings are to be held, the conduct of business at such meetings and the number of members`
  line `necessary to form a quorum thereat;`
  line
  line `^2[(aa) the summoning and holding of meetings of a committee constituted under section 5A, the`
  line `time and place where such meetings are to be held, the conduct of business at such meetings, and the`
  line `number of members necessary to form a quorum thereat and the fees and allowances payable to the`
  line `members for attending the meetings or any other work of the Authority;]`
  line
  line `(b) the powers and duties of the secretary and chief accounts officer of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) the salaries, allowances and conditions of service of the secretary, chief accounts officer and`
  line `other officers and employees;`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure for the carrying out of the functions of the Authority under Chapter III;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which any application for permission under sub-section (1) of section 13 shall be`
  line `made and the particulars to be furnished in such application;`
  line
  line `(f) the terms and conditions subject to which user of lands and buildings in contravention of plans`
  line `may be continued;`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of communicating the grounds of refusal of permission for development;`
  line
  line `(i) the form of the register of applications for permission and the particulars to be contained in`
  line `such register;`
  line
  line `(j) the management of the properties of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(k) the time and manner of payment of betterment charge; and`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Until the Authority is established under this Act, any regulation which may be made under`
  line `sub-section (1) may be made by the Central Government; and any regulation so made may be altered or`
  line `rescinded by the Authority in exercise of its powers under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Act 4 of 1976, s. 3, for certain words (w.e.f. 24-1-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 56 of 1963, s. 29 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
  line
  line `3. Omitted by Act 56 of 1963, s. 29 (w.e.f. 30-12-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (21398)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 70
  title `Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1976, s. 4, for section 58 (w.e.f. 24-1-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21398&sectionno=58&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `^1[58. Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament.--Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after such rule or regulation is made, before each House of`
  line `Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `regulation, or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation`
  line `shall, thereafter, have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule or regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (21399)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 71
  title `Dissolution of the Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21399&sectionno=59&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government is satisfied that the purposes`
  line `for which the Authority was established under this Act have been substantially achieved so as to render`
  line `the continued existence of the Authority in the opinion of the Central Government unnecessary, that`
  line `Government may by notification in the Official Gazette declare that the Authority shall be dissolved with`
  line `effect from such date as may be specified in the notification; and the Authority shall be deemed to be`
  line `dissolved accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) From the said date--`
  line
  line `(a) all properties, funds and dues which are vested in, or realisable by, the Authority shall vest in,`
  line `or be realisable by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all nazul lands placed at the disposal of the Authority shall revert to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) all liabilities which are enforceable against the Authority shall be enforceable against the`
  line `Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) for the purpose of carrying out any development which has not been fully carried out by the`
  line `Authority and for the purpose of realising properties, funds and dues referred to in clause (a), the`
  line `functions of the Authority shall be discharged by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (21400)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 72
  title `Repeal, etc., and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1996, s. 2, for "Union territory of Delhi" (w.e.f. 21-12-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540&sectionId=21400&sectionno=60&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00009_195761_1517807321540
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the date of constitution of the Authority,--`
  line
  line `(a) the United Provinces Town Improvement Act, 1919 (U.P. Act VIII of 1919), shall cease to`
  line `have effect in the ^1[National capital territory of Delhi]; and`
  line
  line `(b) the Delhi (Control of Building Operations) Act, 1955 (53 of 1955), shall stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the provisions of sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) every officer and other employee serving under the Delhi Improvement Trust or the Delhi`
  line `Development (Provisional) Authority immediately before the date of the constitution of the Authority`
  line `shall, on and from such date, be transferred to and become an officer or other employee of the`
  line `Authority with such designations as the Authority may determine and shall hold office by the same`
  line `tenure, at the same remuneration and on the same terms and conditions of service as he would have`
  line `held the same if the Authority had not been constituted, and shall continue to do so unless and until`
  line `such tenure, remuneration and terms and conditions are duly altered by the Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that any service rendered by any such officer or other employee before the constitution`
  line `of the Authority shall be deemed to be service rendered under it:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Authority may employ any such officer or other employee in the`
  line `discharge of such functions under this Act as it may think proper and every such officer or other`
  line `employee shall discharge those functions accordingly;`
  line
  line `(b) anything done or any action taken (including any appointment, delegation, notification, order,`
  line `scheme, permission, rule, bye-law, regulation or form made, granted or issued) under any of the`
  line `aforesaid Acts, shall, so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, continue in force`
  line `and be deemed to have been done or taken under the provisions of this Act unless and until it is`
  line `superseded by anything done or any action taken under the said provisions;`
  line
  line `(c) all debts, obligations and liabilities incurred, all contracts entered into and all matters and`
  line `things engaged to be done by, with or for the Delhi Improvement Trust or the Delhi Development`
  line `(Provisional) Authority shall be deemed to have been incurred, entered into or engaged to be done by,`
  line `with or for the Authority;`
  line
  line `(d) all properties movable and immovable vested in the Delhi Improvement Trust or the Delhi`
  line `Development (Provisional) Authority shall vest in the Authority;`
  line
  line `(e) all rents, fees and other sums of money due to the Delhi Improvement Trust or the Delhi`
  line `Development (Provisional) Authority shall be deemed to be due to the Authority;`
  line
  line `(f) all suits, prosecutions and other legal proceedings instituted or which might have been`
  line `instituted by, for or against the Delhi Improvement Trust or the Delhi Development (Provisional)`
  line `Authority may be continued or instituted by, for or against the Authority.`
